<ns4264:section xmlns:ns4264="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.swing.developingSwingInterfaces.layoutManagersIntroduction.cardLayout">    
        <ns4265:title xmlns:ns4265="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">CardLayout</ns4265:title>
        <ns4266:para xmlns:ns4266="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns4267:literal xmlns:ns4267="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">CardLayout</ns4267:literal> arranges components ontop of one another
          like a stack of cards. Only one component will thus be displayed at a time.</ns4266:para>
        <ns4268:para xmlns:ns4268="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">One of the uses of <ns4269:literal xmlns:ns4269="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">CardLayout</ns4269:literal> is when one wants
          to display a series of dialog boxes (for example in an installation program). The card
          layout supplies serviecs for showing the previous or next card.</ns4268:para>
        <ns4270:para xmlns:ns4270="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"/>
